If in a formula $P = \frac{xm}{S + m t}$, $x$, $m$, $S$, and $t$ are all positive constants, and both $m$ and $S$ are increased simultaneously, while $x$ and $t$ are kept constant, then $P$:
{Select the correct answer without choices provided yet}
$\textbf{(A)}\ \text{Increases}\qquad\textbf{(B)}\ \text{Decreases}\qquad\textbf{(C)}\ \text{Remains constant}\qquad\textbf{(D)}\ \text{Increases slightly}\qquad$

